s not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67BB40E2-722B-1014-9960-DC1902C3897F","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Registry' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          registry = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Registry' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          registry = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.","rule_id":"SV-278932r1141916","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","id":"V-278932"},"group_id":"V-278932","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Success\" selected.","rule_id_src":"SV-278932r1141916_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-278932","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:278932","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5471","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WN11-AU-000587","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67BB4AF5-722B-1014-BDF1-EAF076E23E4A","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     false ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.","rule_id":"SV-278933r1141919","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","id":"V-278933"},"group_id":"V-278933","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_id_src":"SV-278933r1141919_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-278933","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:278933","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5471","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WN11-AU-000588","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67BB5376-722B-1014-9654-EC937BD34A6F","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          sensitive_privilege_use = 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_FAILURE' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          sensitive_privilege_use = 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must block consumer account user authentication.","rule_id":"SV-279688r1153564","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-279688"},"group_id":"V-279688","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Configure the following Group Policy:\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Account \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 11 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center &gt;&gt; Devices &gt;&gt; Configuration &gt;&gt; Create &gt;&gt; New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for consumer under the Settings picker. Under the Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft account category, check the box next to \"Block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\". Click the Enabled radio button, then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","rule_id_src":"SV-279688r1153564_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-279688","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:279688","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5471","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"WN11-00-000126","check_content":"Verify the \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" is enabled.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftAccount\n\nValue Name: DisableUserAuth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the registry value is not \"1\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"67BB5BB4-722B-1014-A7D8-A743607078B0","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe Copilot Rewrite functionality within Notepad and Image Generation within Paint is dependent upon the use of AI credits from a Microsoft 365 Personal or Family subscription. Organizational users must not use personal accounts to login to applications on enterprise machines.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:52:15\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Prevent enabling lock screen camera' is set to 'Enabled')\n"}],"size":263,"uuid":"677F401D-722B-1014-B949-B81E5231A214","display_name":"Microsoft Windows 11","stig_id":"Microsoft_Windows_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"2"},{"stig_name":"Mozilla Firefox Security Technical Implementation Guide","reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","rules":[{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The installed version of Firefox must be supported.","rule_id":"SV-251545r961683","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-251545"},"group_id":"V-251545","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Upgrade the version of the browser to an approved version by obtaining software from the vendor or other trusted source.","rule_id_src":"SV-251545r961683_rule","status":"not_reviewed","group_id_src":"V-251545","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:questionnaire:101","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-ocil.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000001","check_content":"Run Firefox. Click the ellipsis button &gt;&gt; Help &gt;&gt; About Firefox, and view the version number.\n\nIf the Firefox version is not a supported version, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7017FF70-722B-1014-9E24-954DE653F4E1","discussion":"Using versions of an application that are not supported by the vendor is not permitted. Vendors respond to security flaws with updates and patches. These updates are not available for unsupported versions, which can leave the application vulnerable to attack.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-251545, SV-251545r961683, SRG-APP-000456)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000560","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above.","rule_id":"SV-251546r961869","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-001453"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000560","id":"V-251546"},"group_id":"V-251546","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Minimum SSL version enabled\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: TLS 1.2   (or TLS 1.3)\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;SSLVersionMin&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;string&gt;tls1.2&lt;/string&gt;   (or &lt;string&gt;tls1.3&lt;/string&gt;)\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.2\"   or (\"SSLVersionMin\": \"tls1.3\")","rule_id_src":"SV-251546r961869_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251546","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:101","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"high","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000002","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"SSLVersionMin\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"tls1.2\" or \"tls1.3\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70180B6C-722B-1014-9AB8-A2AE04E86A85","discussion":"Use of versions prior to TLS 1.2 are not permitted. SSL 2.0 and SSL 3.0 contain a number of security flaws. These versions must be disabled in compliance with the Network Infrastructure and Secure Remote Computing STIGs.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to allow only TLS 1.2 or above)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SSLVersionMin'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000177","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.","rule_id":"SV-251547r1067550","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000187"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000177","id":"V-251547"},"group_id":"V-251547","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;security.default_personal_cert&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;Ask Every Time&lt;/string&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"security.default_personal_cert\": {\n    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251547r1067550_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251547","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251547","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000003","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"security.default_personal_cert\" with a value of \"Ask Every Time\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701814BA-722B-1014-8C23-B505B9714CC1","discussion":"When a website asks for a certificate for user authentication, Firefox must be configured to have the user choose which certificate to present. Websites within DOD require user authentication for access, which increases security for DOD information. Access will be denied to the user if certificate management is not configured.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox must be configured to ask which certificate to present to a website when a certificate is required.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"security.default_personal_cert\": \\{    \"Value\": \"Ask Every Time\",    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically check for updated versions of installed search plugins.","rule_id":"SV-251548r1067552","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251548"},"group_id":"V-251548","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;browser.search.update&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;false/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.search.update\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251548r1067552_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251548","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251548","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000004","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.search.update\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70181DBE-722B-1014-B9DD-E9B83BFFAE50","discussion":"Updates must be controlled and installed from authorized and trusted servers. This setting overrides a number of other settings that may direct the application to access external URLs.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox must be configured to not automatically check for updated versions of installed search plugins.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"browser.search.update\": \\{    \"Value\": false,    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins.","rule_id":"SV-251549r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251549"},"group_id":"V-251549","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Extensions\nPolicy Name: Extension Update\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;ExtensionUpdate&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"ExtensionUpdate\": false","rule_id_src":"SV-251549r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251549","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:104","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000005","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"ExtensionUpdate\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018267E-722B-1014-8470-86B046C665A4","discussion":"Set this to false to disable checking for updated versions of the Extensions/Themes. Automatic updates from untrusted sites puts the enclave at risk of attack and may override security settings.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not automatically update installed add-ons and plugins)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\ExtensionUpdate'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not automatically execute or download MIME types that are not authorized for auto-download.","rule_id":"SV-251550r961194","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-251550"},"group_id":"V-251550","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Remove any unauthorized extensions from the auto-download list.","rule_id_src":"SV-251550r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id_src":"V-251550","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251550","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000006","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences\" in the browser address bar. \n\nType \"Applications\" in the Find bar in the upper-right corner. \n\nDetermine if any of the following file extensions are listed: HTA, JSE, JS, MOCHA, SHS, VBE, VBS, SCT, WSC, FDF, XFDF, LSL, LSO, LSS, IQY, RQY, DOS, BAT, PS, EPS, WCH, WCM, WB1, WB3, WCH, WCM, AD.\n\nIf the entry exists and the \"Action\" is \"Save File\" or \"Always Ask\", this is not a finding.\n \nIf an extension exists and the entry in the Action column is associated with an application that does/can execute the code, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70182F05-722B-1014-9C66-CA9FFFA1A52D","discussion":"Some files can be downloaded or execute without user interaction. This setting ensures these files are not downloaded and executed.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check all Firefox Profiles for MIME types)\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable form fill assistance.","rule_id":"SV-251551r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251551"},"group_id":"V-251551","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Form History\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableFormHistory&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFormHistory\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251551r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251551","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:106","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000007","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableFormHistory\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701837BF-722B-1014-94A3-F949328FD5AA","discussion":"To protect privacy and sensitive data, Firefox provides the ability to configure the program so that data entered into forms is not saved. This mitigates the risk of a website gleaning private information from prefilled information.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to disable form fill assistance)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableFormHistory'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not use a password store with or without a master password.","rule_id":"SV-251552r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251552"},"group_id":"V-251552","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: PasswordManager\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;PasswordManagerEnabled&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"PasswordManagerEnabled\": false","rule_id_src":"SV-251552r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251552","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:107","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000008","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"PasswordManagerEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018406A-722B-1014-B5FE-B86F7C667B84","discussion":"Firefox can be set to store passwords for sites visited by the user. These individual passwords are stored in a file and can be protected by a master password. Autofill of the password can then be enabled when the site is visited. This feature could also be used to autofill the certificate PIN, which could lead to compromise of DoD information.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not use a password store with or without a master password)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\PasswordManagerEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to block pop-up windows.","rule_id":"SV-251553r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251553"},"group_id":"V-251553","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Popups\nPolicy Name: Block pop-ups from websites\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nPolicy Name: Do not allow preferences to be changed\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nOptional:\nPolicy Name: Allowed Sites\nPolicy State: Enabled\nClick \"Show...\" and enter a list of websites to be allowlisted.\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;PopupBlocking&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Allow&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;array&gt;\n      &lt;string&gt;http://example.mil&lt;/string&gt;\n      &lt;string&gt;http://example.gov&lt;/string&gt;\n    &lt;/array&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Default&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Locked&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"PopupBlocking\": {\n      \"Allow\": [\"http://example.mil/\",\n                \"http://example.gov/\"],\n      \"Default\": true,\n      \"Locked\": true}","rule_id_src":"SV-251553r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251553","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:108","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000009","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"true\", this is a finding.\nIf \"PopupBlocking\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Locked\" \"true\", this is a finding.\n\n\"PopupBlocking\" \"Enabled\" may be used to specify an allowlist of sites where pop-ups are desired, this is optional.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70184978-722B-1014-946C-D04C6CE032B3","discussion":"Pop-up windows may be used to launch an attack within a new browser window with altered settings. This setting blocks pop-up windows created while the page is loading.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to block pop-up windows)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\PopupBlocking\\Default'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox pop-up preferences are locked)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\PopupBlocking\\Locked'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.","rule_id":"SV-251554r1067554","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251554"},"group_id":"V-251554","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;dom.disable_window_move_resize&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251554r1067554_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251554","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251554","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000010","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_move_resize\" with a value of  \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018523F-722B-1014-8F94-C70F5BD75A1B","discussion":"JavaScript can make changes to the browser's appearance. This activity can help disguise an attack taking place in a minimized background window. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from moving and resizing browser windows.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from moving or resizing windows.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"dom.disable_window_move_resize\": \\{    \"Value\": true,    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows.","rule_id":"SV-251555r1067556","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251555"},"group_id":"V-251555","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;dom.disable_window_flip&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"dom.disable_window_flip\": {\n    \"Value\": true,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251555r1067556_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251555","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251555","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000011","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"dom.disable_window_flip\" with a value of \"true\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70185B7B-722B-1014-80F1-D72A40D40ED1","discussion":"JavaScript can raise and lower browser windows to cause improper input. Configure the browser setting to prevent scripts on visited websites from raising and lowering browser windows.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox must be configured to prevent JavaScript from raising or lowering windows)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"dom.disable_window_flip\": \\{    \"Value\": true,    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to disable the installation of extensions.","rule_id":"SV-251557r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251557"},"group_id":"V-251557","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Addons\nPolicy Name: Allow add-on installs from websites\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;InstallAddonsPermission&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"InstallAddonsPermission\": {\n      \"Default\": false\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251557r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251557","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:112","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000013","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"InstallAddonsPermission\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Default\" \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701863FF-722B-1014-91CE-D260A5F6251B","discussion":"A browser extension is a program that has been installed into the browser to add functionality. Where a plug-in interacts only with a web page and usually a third-party external application (e.g., Flash, Adobe Reader), an extension interacts with the browser program itself. Extensions are not embedded in web pages and must be downloaded and installed in order to work. Extensions allow browsers to avoid restrictions that apply to web pages. \n\nFor example, an extension can be written to combine data from multiple domains and present it when a certain page is accessed, which can be considered cross-site scripting. If a browser is configured to allow unrestricted use of extensions, plug-ins can be loaded and installed from malicious sources and used on the browser.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to disable the installation of extensions)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\InstallAddonsPermission\\Default'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Background submission of information to Mozilla must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251558r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251558"},"group_id":"V-251558","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Telemetry\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableTelemetry&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableTelemetry\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251558r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251558","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:113","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000014","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableTelemetry\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70186CF6-722B-1014-8810-F531D751CCF6","discussion":"Firefox by default sends information about Firefox to Mozilla servers. There should be no background submission of technical and other information from DoD computers to Mozilla with portions posted publicly.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Background submission of information to Mozilla is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableTelemetry'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox development tools must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251559r961167","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000266","id":"V-251559"},"group_id":"V-251559","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Developer Tools\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableDeveloperTools&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableDeveloperTools\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251559r961167_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251559","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:114","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000015","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisableDeveloperTools\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018780E-722B-1014-A3AD-BCF2D89A148B","discussion":"Information needed by an attacker to begin looking for possible vulnerabilities in a web browser includes any information about the web browser and plug-ins or modules being used. When debugging or trace information is enabled in a production web browser, information about the web browser, such as web browser type, version, patches installed, plug-ins and modules installed, type of code being used by the hosted application, and any back ends being used for data storage may be displayed. Because this information may be placed in logs and general messages during normal operation of the web browser, an attacker does not have to cause an error condition to gain this information.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox development tools are disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableDeveloperTools'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.","rule_id":"SV-251560r1067559","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-251560"},"group_id":"V-251560","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Install the DOD root certificates. Other AO-approved certificates may also be used. Certificates designed for SIPRNet may be used as appropriate.\n\nOn Windows, import certificates from the operating system by using Certificates &gt;&gt; Import Enterprise Roots (Certificates) via policy or Group Policy Object (GPO).","rule_id_src":"SV-251560r1067559_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251560","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251560","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000016","check_content":"Type \"about:preferences#privacy\" in the browser window. \n\nScroll down to the bottom and select \"View Certificates...\".\n\nIn the Certificate Manager window, select the \"Authorities\" tab.\n\nScroll through the Certificate Name list to the U.S. Government heading. Look for the entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5.\n\nIf there are entries for DOD Root CA 3, DOD Root CA 4, and DOD Root CA 5, select them individually.\n\nClick \"View\".\n\nVerify the issuer name is \"US Government\".\n\nIf there are no entries for the appropriate DOD root certificates, this is a finding. If other AO-approved certificates are used, this is not a finding. If SIPRNet-specific certificates are used, this is not a finding.\n\nNote: In a Windows environment, use of policy setting \"security.enterprise_roots.enabled=true\" will point Firefox to the Windows Trusted Root Certification Authority Store. This is not a finding. It can also be set via the policy Certificates &gt;&gt; ImportEnterpriseRoots, which can be verified via \"about:policies\".","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70188264-722B-1014-AADC-AECBBBDCB7F2","discussion":"The DOD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DOD Certificate Authority (CA).","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox must have the DOD root certificates installed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Certificates\\ImportEnterpriseRoots'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Verify DOD root certificates are installed)\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000326","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must prevent the user from quickly deleting data.","rule_id":"SV-251562r987660","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-002355"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000326","id":"V-251562"},"group_id":"V-251562","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Forget Button\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableForgetButton&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableForgetButton\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251562r987660_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251562","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:117","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000018","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableForgetButton\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70188BD8-722B-1014-87AE-F57DAD337057","discussion":"There should not be an option for a user to \"forget\" work they have done. This is required to meet non-repudiation controls.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox prevents the user from quickly deleting data)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableForgetButton'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox private browsing must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251563r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251563"},"group_id":"V-251563","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Private Browsing\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisablePrivateBrowsing&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePrivateBrowsing\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251563r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251563","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:118","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000019","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"DisablePrivateBrowsing\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701895C5-722B-1014-98C9-B75B0B8DCC11","discussion":"Private browsing allows the user to browse the internet without recording their browsing history/activity. From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable. Best practice requires that browser history is retained.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox private browsing is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisablePrivateBrowsing'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox search suggestions must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251564r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251564"},"group_id":"V-251564","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Search\nPolicy Name: Search Suggestions\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;SearchSuggestEnabled&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SearchSuggestEnabled\": false","rule_id_src":"SV-251564r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251564","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:119","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000020","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window.\n\nIf \"SearchSuggestEnabled\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70189E7F-722B-1014-B2B7-ABCE53C744E8","discussion":"Search suggestions must be disabled as this could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox search suggestions is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SearchSuggestEnabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox autoplay must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251565r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251565"},"group_id":"V-251565","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Permissions\\Autoplay\nPolicy Name: Default autoplay level\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Block Audio and Video\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Permissions&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Autoplay&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;block-audio-video&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n \nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Permissions\": {\n  \"Autoplay\": {\n    \"Default\": \"block-audio-video\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251565r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251565","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:120","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"low","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000021","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Permissions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Autoplay\" with a value of \"Default\" and \"Block-audio-video\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018A6F0-722B-1014-B15D-F228F5FB5D2A","discussion":"Autoplay allows the user to control whether videos can play automatically (without user consent) with audio content. The user must be able to select content that is run within the browser window.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox autoplay is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Permissions\\Autoplay\\Default'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox network prediction must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251566r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251566"},"group_id":"V-251566","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Network Prediction\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;NetworkPrediction&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"NetworkPrediction\": false","rule_id_src":"SV-251566r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251566","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:121","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000022","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser window. \n\nIf \"NetworkPrediction\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018AF51-722B-1014-B386-DD918C885C34","discussion":"If network prediction is enabled, requests to URLs are made without user consent. The browser should always make a direct DNS request without prefetching occurring.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox network prediction is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\NetworkPrediction'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox fingerprinting protection must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-251567r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251567"},"group_id":"V-251567","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Fingerprinting\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;EnableTrackingProtection&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Fingerprinting&lt;/key&gt;\n &lt;true/&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Fingerprinting\": true\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251567r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251567","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:122","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000023","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Fingerprinting\"  with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018B79F-722B-1014-886E-F5EDFDB6F820","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nFingerprinting scripts collect information about browser and device configuration, such as operating system, screen resolution, and other settings. By compiling these pieces of data, fingerprinters create a unique profile that can be used to track the user around the web.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox fingerprinting protection is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EnableTrackingProtection\\Fingerprinting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox cryptomining protection must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-251568r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251568"},"group_id":"V-251568","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Tracking Protection\nPolicy Name: Cryptomining\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;EnableTrackingProtection&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Cryptomining&lt;/key&gt;\n &lt;true/&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EnableTrackingProtection\": {\n  \"Cryptomining\": true\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251568r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251568","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:123","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000024","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EnableTrackingProtection\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"Cryptomining\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018BFF1-722B-1014-B67E-F3E6412A9F8E","discussion":"The Content Blocking/Tracking Protection feature stops Firefox from loading content from malicious sites. The content might be a script or an image, for example. If a site is on one of the tracker lists that Firefox is set to use, the fingerprinting script (or other tracking script/image) will not be loaded from that site.\n\nCryptomining scripts use a computer's central processing unit to invisibly mine cryptocurrency.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox Cryptomining protection is enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EnableTrackingProtection\\Cryptomining'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.","rule_id":"SV-251569r1067561","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251569"},"group_id":"V-251569","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;browser.contentblocking.category&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;strict&lt;/string&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n  \"browser.contentblocking.category\": {\n    \"Value\": \"strict\",\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251569r1067561_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251569","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251569","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000025","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not include \"browser.contentblocking.category\" with a value of  \"strict\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018C852-722B-1014-A928-FEF906B751CE","discussion":"Tracking generally refers to content, cookies, or scripts that can collect browsing data across multiple sites.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of nonessential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox Enhanced Tracking Protection must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"browser.contentblocking.category\": \\{    \"Value\": \"strict\",    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251570r1067563","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251570"},"group_id":"V-251570","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Preferences\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value:\n{\n  \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n    \"Value\": false,\n    \"Status\": \"locked\"\n  }\n}\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;Preferences&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Value&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;false/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Status&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;string&gt;locked&lt;/string&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"Preferences\": {\n\"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": {\n\"Value\": false,\n\"Status\": \"locked\"\n},","rule_id_src":"SV-251570r1067563_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251570","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:251570","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000026","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"Preferences\" is not displayed under Policy Name and the Policy Value does not include \"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\" with a value of  \"false\" and status of \"locked\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018D0BC-722B-1014-910A-DE67D93E65AA","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program makes it easier for users to discover extensions that have been reviewed for security, functionality, and user experience. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        '' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to '\"extensions.htmlaboutaddons.recommendations.enabled\": \\{    \"Value\": false,    \"Status\": \"locked\"  }' \n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox deprecated ciphers must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251571r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251571"},"group_id":"V-251571","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Disabled Ciphers\nPolicy Name: TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;DisabledCiphers&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt;\n  &lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisabledCiphers\": {\n  \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\": true\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251571r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251571","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:126","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000027","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar.\n\nIf \"DisabledCiphers\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA\" with a value of  \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018D912-722B-1014-B675-9EF1DE80532C","discussion":"A weak cipher is defined as an encryption/decryption algorithm that uses a key of insufficient length. Using an insufficient length for a key in an encryption/decryption algorithm opens up the possibility (or probability) that the encryption scheme could be broken.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox deprecated ciphers are disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisabledCiphers\\TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser.","rule_id":"SV-251572r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251572"},"group_id":"V-251572","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\User Messaging\nPolicy Name: Extension Recommendations\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;UserMessaging&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;ExtensionRecommendations&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"UserMessaging\": {\n  \"ExtensionRecommendations\": false\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251572r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251572","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:127","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000028","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"UserMessaging\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"ExtensionRecommendations\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018E1BB-722B-1014-98EF-C8E0A878E20D","discussion":"The Recommended Extensions program recommends extensions to users as they surf the web.\n\nThe user must not be encouraged to install extensions from the websites they visit. Allowed extensions are to be centrally managed.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox does not recommend extensions as the user is using the browser)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\UserMessaging\\ExtensionRecommendations'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"The Firefox New Tab page must not show Top Sites, Sponsored Top Sites, Pocket Recommendations, Sponsored Pocket Stories, Searches, Highlights, or Snippets.","rule_id":"SV-251573r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251573"},"group_id":"V-251573","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Customize Firefox Home\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Search\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Top Sites\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Top Sites\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Recommended by Pocket\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Sponsored Pocket Stories\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Download History\"\nPolicy Value: Uncheck \"Snippets\"\nPolicy Value: Check \"Do not allow settings to be changed\"\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;FirefoxHome&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;Search&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;TopSites&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;SponsoredTopSites&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;Pocket&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;SponsoredPocket&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;Highlights&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;Snippets&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n&lt;key&gt;Locked&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;true/&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"FirefoxHome\": {\n  \"Search\": false,\n  \"TopSites\": false,\n  \"SponsoredTopSites\": false,\n  \"Pocket\": false,\n  \"SponsoredPocket\": false,\n  \"Highlights\": false,\n  \"Snippets\": false,\n  \"locked\": true\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251573r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251573","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:128","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000029","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Search\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"TopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredTopSites\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Pocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"SponsoredPocket\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Highlights\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Snippets\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.\nIf \"FirefoxHome\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" with a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018EA47-722B-1014-BB81-F126E769F4CF","discussion":"The New Tab page by default shows a list of built-in top sites, as well as the top sites the user has visited.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.\n\nThe new tab page must not actively show user activity.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Top Sites)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\TopSites'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Sponsored Top Sites)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\SponsoredTopSites'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Pocket Recommendations)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\Pocket'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Sponsored Pocket Stories)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\SponsoredPocket'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Highlights)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\Highlights'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Snippets)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\Snippets'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Customize Firefox Home settings are locked)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\Locked'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (The Firefox New Tab page does not show Search)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\FirefoxHome\\Search'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251577r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251577"},"group_id":"V-251577","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DNS Over HTTPS\nPolicy Name: Enabled\nPolicy State: Disabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;DNSOverHTTPS&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Enabled&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;false/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DNSOverHTTPS\": {\"Enabled\": false}","rule_id_src":"SV-251577r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251577","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:132","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000033","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DNSOverHTTPS\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" with a value of \"false\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018F2AC-722B-1014-AF3C-85267D4764D8","discussion":"DNS over HTTPS has generally not been adopted in the DoD. DNS is tightly controlled.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include, but are not limited to, advertising software or browser plug-ins not related to requirements or providing a wide array of functionality not required for every mission, but cannot be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured so that DNS over HTTPS is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DNSOverHTTPS\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox accounts must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251578r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251578"},"group_id":"V-251578","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Firefox Accounts\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableFirefoxAccounts&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;true/&gt; \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFirefoxAccounts\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251578r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251578","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:133","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000034","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFirefoxAccounts\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"7018FB68-722B-1014-9567-F407C4CE1E78","discussion":"Disable Firefox Accounts integration (Sync). \n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox accounts are disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableFirefoxAccounts'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox feedback reporting must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251580r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251580"},"group_id":"V-251580","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\\nPolicy Name: Disable Feedback Commands\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableFeedbackCommands&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFeedbackCommands\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-251580r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251580","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:135","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000036","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFeedbackCommands\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value is not \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701904A1-722B-1014-A3C2-CF4F434A109B","discussion":"Disable the menus for reporting sites (Submit Feedback, Report Deceptive Site). \n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox feedback reporting is disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableFeedbackCommands'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox encrypted media extensions must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-251581r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-251581"},"group_id":"V-251581","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy Name: Enable Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Lock Encrypted Media Extensions\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;EncryptedMediaExtensions&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;dict&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Enabled&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;false/&gt;\n    &lt;key&gt;Locked&lt;/key&gt;\n    &lt;true/&gt; \n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"EncryptedMediaExtensions\": {\n  \"Enabled\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true\n}","rule_id_src":"SV-251581r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-251581","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:136","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000037","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"EncryptedMediaExtensions\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have \"Enabled\" set to \"false\" or the Policy Value does not have \"Locked\" set to \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70190DD4-722B-1014-A751-B214A7D1866E","discussion":"Enable or disable Encrypted Media Extensions and optionally lock it.\n\nIf \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox does not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) unless the user consents to installing them.\n\nIf \"Locked\" is set to \"true\" and \"Enabled\" is set to \"false\", Firefox will not download encrypted media extensions (such as Widevine) or ask the user to install them.\n\nIt is detrimental for applications to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nApplications are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). \n\nExamples of non-essential capabilities include but are not limited to advertising software or browser plug-ins that are not related to requirements or provide a wide array of functionality not required for every mission but that cannot be disabled.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox encrypted media extensions are disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EncryptedMediaExtensions\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox encrypted media extensions setting is locked)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\EncryptedMediaExtensions\\Locked'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox must be configured to not delete data upon shutdown.","rule_id":"SV-252881r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-252881"},"group_id":"V-252881","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\Clear data when browser is closed\nPolicy Name: Cache, Cookies, Download History, Form &amp; Search History, Browsing History, Active Logins, Site Preferences, Offline Website Data\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Name: Locked\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\nAdd the following:\n&lt;key&gt;SanitizeOnShutdown&lt;/key&gt;\n&lt;dict&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Cache&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Cookies&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Downloads&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;FormData&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;History&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Sessions&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;SiteSettings&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;OfflineApps&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;false/&gt;\n  &lt;key&gt;Locked&lt;/key&gt;\n  &lt;true/&gt;\n&lt;/dict&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"SanitizeOnShutdown\": {\n  \"Cache\": false,\n  \"Cookies\": false,\n  \"Downloads\": false,\n  \"FormData\": false,\n  \"History\": false,\n  \"Sessions\": false,\n  \"SiteSettings\": false,\n  \"OfflineApps\": false,\n  \"Locked\": true \n}","rule_id_src":"SV-252881r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-252881","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.firefox.windows:def:116","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000017","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"SanitizeOnShutdown\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have {\"Cache\":false,\"Cookies\":false,\"Downloads\":false,\"FormData\":false,\"Sessions\":false,\"History\":false,\"OfflineApps\":false,\"SiteSettings\":false,\"Locked\":true}, this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70191727-722B-1014-BD32-C1F6EA585790","discussion":"For diagnostic purposes, data must remain behind when the browser is closed. This is required to meet non-repudiation controls.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Cache upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\Cache'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Cookies upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\Cookies'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Download History upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\Downloads'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Form &amp; Search History upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\FormData'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Browsing History upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\History'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Active Logins upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\Sessions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Site Preferences upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\SiteSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox is configured to not delete Offline Website Data upon shutdown)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\OfflineApps'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Firefox SanitizeOnShutdown settings are locked)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\SanitizeOnShutdown\\Locked'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Pocket must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-252908r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-252908"},"group_id":"V-252908","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Pocket\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;DisablePocket&lt;/key&gt;\n &lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisablePocket\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-252908r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-252908","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:252908","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000038","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisablePocket\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"70191F9A-722B-1014-9491-D28AEB5DF3F8","discussion":"Pocket, previously known as Read It Later, is a social bookmarking service for storing, sharing, and discovering web bookmarks. Data gathering cloud services such as this are generally disabled in the DoD.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox extension recommendations must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisablePocket'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"},{"security_override_guidance":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_title":"Firefox Studies must be disabled.","rule_id":"SV-252909r960963","weight":"10.0","stig_uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"ia_controls":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-252909"},"group_id":"V-252909","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with \"gpedit.msc\".\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Mozilla\\Firefox\nPolicy Name: Disable Firefox Studies\nPolicy State: Enabled\n\nmacOS \"plist\" file:\n&lt;key&gt;DisableFirefoxStudies&lt;/key&gt;\n &lt;true/&gt;\n\nLinux \"policies.json\" file:\nAdd the following in the policies section:\n\"DisableFirefoxStudies\": true","rule_id_src":"SV-252909r960963_rule","status":"open","group_id_src":"V-252909","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.firefox.windows:def:252909","href":"U_MOZ_Firefox_Windows_V6R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV12-oval2.xml"},"reference_identifier":"5446","classification":"Unclassified","potential_impacts":"","severity":"medium","responsibility":"","comments":null,"rule_version":"FFOX-00-000039","check_content":"Type \"about:policies\" in the browser address bar. \n\nIf \"DisableFirefoxStudies\" is not displayed under Policy Name or the Policy Value does not have a value of \"true\", this is a finding.","false_positives":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"uuid":"701928F8-722B-1014-935C-F8B854E88393","discussion":"Studies try out different features and ideas before they are released to all Firefox users. Testing beta software is not in the DoD user's mission.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-04-01T11:54:13\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Firefox Studies must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Mozilla\\Firefox\\DisableFirefoxStudies'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n"}],"size":34,"uuid":"70166886-722B-1014-978D-CDB4D6E613B4","display_name":"Mozilla Firefox","stig_id":"MOZ_Fire